description:
&lt;p&gt;The Trust&#39;s Integrated All Age Eating Disorders Service is a well-respected service locally and nationally and is at the cutting edge of treatment delivery for those with an eating disorder and their families/carers.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;We are looking to recruit mental health outreach support workers to our team.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The successful applicants will have good knowledge and experience of working within a mental health setting, ideally with people who have an eating disorder. They will be able to demonstrate initiative and a clear ability to work practically, to help promote recovery.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Other desirable experience includes working in a community service with patients, their families and carers and working within a multi-disciplinary team. Outreach work involves working in the patient’s own environment.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The successful applicants will offer high quality, evidenced based interventions and ensure high standards of care when working with people with an Eating Disorder and their families.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Car driver essential subject to the provisions of the Equality Act 2010.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Full or part time hours are available.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;In return we will offer you support to develop in the role and in your career.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will be required to undertake a &lt;strong&gt;Prevention and Management of Violence and Aggression course&lt;/strong&gt; and it is a condition of your employment that you successfully complete all aspects of this course; if this is not achieved you will not be able to commence working in the post.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;If you are interested in moving to Dorset, we also offer a generous relocation package of up to £5,000. For further details on relocation expenses please email dhc.careers@nhs.net.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Employment in this post requires an Enhanced Disclosure and Barring Service (DBS) check. The DBS levies a charge of £40 and the Trust will recover this cost in instalments from your first 3 salary payments. This will only apply to candidates who are new to the Trust and not internal staff.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;Applicants who subscribe to the DBS update service and are able to present a valid DBS certificate will not incur a charge.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Name: Zainab Abdul-Raheem Job title: Ward Manager&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Email address: Zainab.Abdul-Raheem@nhs.net Telephone number: 01202 492147&lt;/p&gt;
